         MACRO                                                          00160000
.*                                                                      00170000
.* This macro handles the stack of DC modifications for use by the      00180000
.* DC macro, which replaces the assembler's DC instruction              00190000
.*                                                                      00200000
&LABEL   DCOVR &OPT,                   * Parameters are in &SYSLIST    *00210000
               &NEWNAM                 * New name for *NEWNAME option   00220000
.*                                                                      00230000
.* &LABEL mandatory, except when &OPT=*END                              00240000
.*        To specify an override for an unlabeled DC, specify the label 00250000
.*        of the last preceding labeled DC and the relative number of   00260000
.*        the unlabeled statement to be overridden. E.g.: LABEG+3,      00270000
.*        would  mean the third unlabeled DC after the DC with label    00280000
.*        LABEG.                                                        00290000
.* &OPT   specifies one of the following:                               00300000
.*        *END cancels all outstanding DCOVR requests                   00310000
.*        *DS  changes the DC into a DS, which may in turn be           00320000
.*             overridden using the DSOVR macro                         00330000
.*        *SUPPRESS suppresses the definition of &LABEL                 00340000
.*        *NEWNAME changes the DC for &LABEL into one for &NEWNAM,      00350000
.*              i.e. Specify *NEWNAME,newname,parmstring                00360000
.*        Other values override the DC-operand string                   00370000
.* &NEWNAM Specifies the new name, if &OPT=*NEWNAME                     00380000
.*        &NEWNAM may optionally be followed by a parameter string      00390000
.*        If &NEWNAM specifies *NONAME the DC will become unlabeled     00400000
.* &SYSLIST Specifies an operand string, which replaces the complete    00410000
.*        operand string of the original DC statement.                  00420000
.*                                                                      00430000
.********************************************************************** 00431001
